parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power and mobility, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission fails to engage
the transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle loses power or acceleration
the transmission warning light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear differential seal can cause the differential to leak fluid, leading to premature wear and potential failure of the differential, which can cause loss of vehicle control and accidents.
symptoms: Rear differential fluid leak
unusual noises or vibrations from the rear of the vehicle
difficulty shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the shift lever can cause difficulty or inability to shift gears, leading to loss of vehicle control and accidents.
symptoms: The shift lever is difficult to move or stuck
the shift lever requires excessive force to move
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The poor design of the windshield can cause it to crack and pop out of the frame, obstructing the driver's view and potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: Windshield cracks
windshield pops out of the frame
multiple pieces of glass in the windshield.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The disintegration of foam in the air ducts can cause debris to be blown into the cabin, potentially obstructing the driver's view or causing a distraction, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: White foam pieces coming out of the air ducts.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake System Failure due to Obstruction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The obstruction in the brake line can cause the brakes to drag, leading to excessive wear and potentially catastrophic failures, such as the tag axle breaking off, which can result in accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Brake repairs are required frequently
the brakes feel spongy or soft
the vehicle pulls to one side while braking
the brakes overheat
the tag axle fails
the vehicle is difficult to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Inaccurate Gross Vehicle Weight Rating (GVWR) Information
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inaccurate GVWR information can lead to overloaded vehicles, which can cause brake system failures, axle failures, and other safety-critical component failures, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle is overweight
the brakes are prone to failure
the axles are prone to failure
the vehicle handles poorly
the vehicle is difficult to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Lack of Warranty Coverage due to Dispute between Manufacturers
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The dispute between manufacturers can leave vehicle owners without warranty coverage, forcing them to bear the cost of repairs, which can lead to unsafe vehicles being driven on the road.
symptoms: The vehicle owner is denied warranty coverage
the vehicle owner is forced to pay for repairs out of pocket
the vehicle is not repaired properly
the vehicle remains in an unsafe condition.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden blowout of one or multiple Michelin tires can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and damage to the vehicle, potentially leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Sudden and unexpected tire blowout
often accompanied by a loud noise
loss of vehicle control
and potential damage to the wheel well or surrounding areas.
